q: You are given an integer array representing recorded measurements. A value is considered a spike if it is at least three times greater than the maximum of all previous values. 
op: Return the 0-based index of the first spike in the array. If no spike is found, return -1. 
Example 
metrics = [3, 10, 2, 7] 
Output: 1 

Explanation: Index 0 → value = 3 → initial maximum 
Index 1 → value = 10 
10 >= 3 * 3 = 9 → spike detected 

